cs.CR, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the use of distributed ledger technology (DLT) to ensure the integrity of digital documents stored within public archives. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with ensuring the authenticity and immutability of data. The use of DLT also falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DL) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the provenance and searchability of archived documents, which falls under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
